cs.DC, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on evaluating the performance of distributed deep learning frameworks on GPUs, which involves parallel computing and cluster computing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper deals with deep learning frameworks and neural networks, which are subfields of machine learning. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The paper benchmarks the performance of the frameworks on three popular convolutional neural networks, which are widely used in computer vision tasks. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing): The paper discusses the training of deep neural networks, which is a subfield of neural computing. 
- cs.SC (Performance): The paper evaluates the running performance of the frameworks and identifies bottlenecks and overheads, which are related to system performance.
